25 def hampel_filter_forloop(input_series, window_size, n_sigmas=3):
26  """
27  Implementation of Hampel Filter for outlier detection.
28 
29  Arguments
30  ----------
31  `input_series`: `np.array`
32  The input data to use for outlier detection.
33 
34  `window_size`: `int`
35  The sliding window size to use for the filter on
36  `input_series`.
37 
38  `n_sigmas`: `int`
39  The number of standard deviations to determine
40  what data points are outliers.
41  """
42  n = len(input_series)
43  new_series = input_series.copy()
44  k = 1.4826 # scale factor for Gaussian distribution
45  indices = []
46  # possibly use np.nanmedian
47  for i in range((window_size), (n - window_size)):
48  x0 = np.median(input_series[(i - window_size):(i + window_size)])
49  S0 = k * np.median(np.abs(input_series[(i - window_size):(i + window_size)] - x0))
50  if (np.abs(input_series[i] - x0) > n_sigmas * S0):
51  new_series[i] = x0
52  indices.append(i)
53  return new_series, indices

56 class DynamicPoseData():
57  """
58  Class to store dynamic pose data into a nested dictionary.
59  It is stored as in [20 poses][7 excited joints][7 IMUs][data].
60  self.data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name] = np.ndarray
61  The data is defined as below.
62  data = [max acceleration, theta at the point].
63  """
64  def __init__(self, pose_names, joint_names, imu_names, filepath):

66  Initialize StaticPoseData class.
67 
68  Arguments
69  ----------
70  pose_names: list[str]
71  Names of poses
72  joint_names: list[str]
73  Names of joints
74  imu_names: list[str]
75  Names of imus
76  filepath: str
77  Path to save the collected data
78  """

113  def clean_data(self, verbose=False):
114  """
115  Cleans the data.
116 
117  Arguments
118  ----------
119  `verbose`: `bool`
120  """
121  # Create nested dictionary to store data
122  data = copy.deepcopy(self.data)
123  for pose_name in self.pose_names:
124  for joint_name in self.joint_names:
125  for imu_name in self.imu_names:
126  d = self.data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name][2:, :]
127  norms = np.linalg.norm(d[:, :3], axis=1)
128  norms, outliers_index = hampel_filter_forloop(norms, 10, 1)
129  idx = np.argmax(norms)
130 
131  # Save maximum angular velocity A of all time
132  w = d[:, 3]
133  w, outliers_index = hampel_filter_forloop(w, 10, 1)
134  max_w_idx = np.argmax(w)
135 
136  joint_accel = d[:, 4]
137  ja, outliers_index = hampel_filter_forloop(joint_accel, 10, 1)
138  # max_ja_idx = np.argmax(ja)
139  """
140  joints = d[:, 4:]
141  window = 50
142  rospy.loginfo(
143  utils.n2s(
144  self.data[pose_name]
145  [joint_name]
146  [imu_name][idx-window:idx+window+1, :7], 3))
147  if joint_name == self.joint_names[0]
148  and (imu_name in self.imu_names[:2]):
149  rospy.loginfo(
150  '[%s, %s, %s]'%(pose_name, joint_name, imu_name))
151  rospy.loginfo(utils.n2s(d[:window+1, :9], 3))
152  rospy.loginfo(
153  '[%ith Norm=%.3f (%.2f, %.2f, %.2f),
154  w=%.2f, joint accel=%.2f'%\
155  (idx, norms[idx], d[idx,0],
156  d[idx,1], d[idx,2], w[idx], ja[idx]))
157  rospy.loginfo(
158  '[%ith Norm=%.3f (%.2f, %.2f, %.2f),
159  w=%.2f, joint accel=%.2f'%\
160  (max_w_idx,
161  norms[max_w_idx], d[max_w_idx,0],
162  d[max_w_idx,1], d[max_w_idx,2],
163  w[max_w_idx], ja[max_w_idx]))
164  rospy.loginfo('[%ith Norm=%.3f (%.2f, %.2f, %.2f),
165  w=%.2f, joint accel=%.2f'%\
166  (max_ja_idx, norms[max_ja_idx],
167  d[max_ja_idx,0], d[max_ja_idx,1],
168  d[max_ja_idx,2], w[max_ja_idx], ja[max_ja_idx]))
169  """
170 
171  data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name] = self.data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name][idx, :]
172  data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name][3] = w[idx]
173  data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name][4] = w[max_w_idx]
174 
175  if verbose:
176  rospy.loginfo(data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name])
177  d = data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name]
178  rospy.loginfo('[%s, %s, %s] (%.3f, %.3f, %.3f)'
179  % (pose_name, joint_name, imu_name, d[0], d[1], d[2]))
180  return data

198 class DynamicPoseDataSaver():
199  """
200  Class for collecting dynamic pose data and save them as a pickle file

202  def __init__(self, controller, poses_list, filepath='data/dynamic_data'):
203  """
204  Initializes DynamicPoseDataSaver class.
205 
206  Arguments
207  -----------
208  controller:
209  Wrapped controller to control either Panda or Sawyer robot.
210  poses_list: list
211  A list of poses. Each pose is a list.
212  It includes 7 joint position, 7 joint velociites, and Pose name
213  filepath: str
214  File path to save the collected data
215  """
216  self.controller = controller
217  self.poses_list = poses_list
218 
219  # constant
220  # TODO: get imu names automatically
221  self.pose_names = [pose[2] for pose in poses_list]
222  self.joint_names = self.controller.joint_names
223  self.imu_names = ['imu_link0', 'imu_link1', 'imu_link2',
224  'imu_link3', 'imu_link4', 'imu_link5', 'imu_link6']
225  self.imu_topics = ['imu_data0', 'imu_data1', 'imu_data2',
226  'imu_data3', 'imu_data4', 'imu_data5', 'imu_data6']
227 
228  self.ready = False
229  self.curr_positions = [0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0]
230  self.curr_pose_name = self.pose_names[0]
231  self.curr_joint_name = self.joint_names[0]
232  self.max_angular_velocity = -np.inf
233  self.prev_w = 0.0
234  self.prev_t = 0.000001
235  self.curr_acc = 0.0
236 
237  rospy.loginfo(self.joint_names)
238 
239  # data storage
240  self.data_storage = DynamicPoseData(self.pose_names, self.joint_names, self.imu_names, filepath)
241  rospy.sleep(1)
242  # Subscribe to IMUs
243  for imu_topic in self.imu_topics:
244  rospy.Subscriber(imu_topic, Imu, self.callback)

246  def callback(self, data):
247  """
248  A callback function for IMU topics
249 
250  Arguments
251  ----------
252  data: sensor_msgs.msg.Imu
253  IMU data. Please refer to the official documentation.
254  http://docs.ros.org/melodic/api/sensor_msgs/html/msg/Imu.html
255  """
256  if self.ready:
257  accel = data.linear_acceleration
258  joint_angles = [self.controller.joint_angle(name) for name in self.joint_names]
259 
260  if self.curr_joint_name == self.joint_names[0] and data.header.frame_id == 'imu_link0':
261  pass
262  # rospy.loginfo(utils.n2s(
263  # np.array([accel.x, accel.y, accel.z])))
264 
265  curr_t = rospy.get_rostime().to_sec()
266  dt = curr_t - self.prev_t
267 
268  curr_w = self.controller.joint_velocity(self.curr_joint_name)
269  curr_A = abs(curr_w)
270 
271  try:
272  self.curr_acc = (curr_w - self.prev_w) / dt
273  except Exception:
274  pass
275 
276  if curr_A > self.max_angular_velocity:
277  self.max_angular_velocity = curr_A
278  # rospy.loginfo(self.curr_joint_name + ' ' + data.header.frame_id + ' ' + Max Angular Velocity: %.4f'%(curr_A))
279 
280  self.data_storage.append(
281  self.curr_pose_name, # for each defined initial pose
282  self.curr_joint_name, # for each excited joint
283  data.header.frame_id, # for each imu
284  np.array([accel.x, accel.y, accel.z,
285  self.max_angular_velocity, self.curr_acc] + joint_angles))
286 
287  self.prev_w = curr_w
288  self.prev_t = curr_t

290  def move_like_sine_dynamic(self):
291  """
292  This will move the joint of the robot arm like a sine wave
293  for all joints for all defined poses.
294  """
295  self.controller.set_joint_position_speed(speed=1.0)
296 
297  freq = rospy.get_param('/oscillation_frequency')
298  A = rospy.get_param('/oscillation_magnitude')
299 
300  for pose in self.poses_list:
301  positions, _, pose_name = pose[0], pose[1], pose[2] # noqa: F841
302  self.curr_positions = positions
303  self.curr_pose_name = pose_name
304  self.controller.publish_positions(positions, sleep=1)
305  print('At Position: ' + pose_name,
306  map(int, RAD2DEG*np.array(positions)))
307 
308  for i, joint_name in enumerate(self.joint_names):
309  self.curr_joint_name = joint_name
310  self.max_angular_velocity = -np.inf
311  self.prev_w = self.controller.joint_velocity(self.curr_joint_name)
312  self.prev_t = rospy.get_rostime().to_sec()
313 
314  # Prepare for publishing a trajectory
315  velocities = np.zeros(len(self.joint_names))
316  accelerations = np.zeros(len(self.joint_names))
317  poss = copy.deepcopy(positions)
318 
319  # stopping time
320  self.ready = True
321  now = rospy.get_rostime()
322  while True:
323  t = (rospy.get_rostime() - now).to_sec()
324 
325  # Oscillated Pos, Vel, Acc
326  position = A/(2*pi*freq)*(1-math.cos(2 * pi * freq * t))
327  velocity = A*math.sin(2 * pi * freq * t)
328  acceleration = 2*pi*freq*A*math.cos(2 * pi * freq * t)
329 
330  poss[i] = positions[i] + position
331  velocities[i] = velocity
332  accelerations[i] = acceleration
333 
334  self.controller.publish_trajectory(poss, velocities, accelerations, None)
335 
336  if t > OSCILLATION_TIME:
337  break
338 
339  self.ready = False
340  rospy.sleep(1)
